WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
EX-CITY ATTORNEY HIRED 
The Culver City Council approved contracting legal assistance from former city 
attorney Joseph Pannone for projects such as Marina Place, Playa Vista and the 
city's environmental regulations. 
Pannone's firm, Kane, Ballmer and Berkman, will be paid $115 per hour for his 
services. Pannone joined the firm last November after 10 years with the city. 
Eleanor Egan will become city attorney on Feb. 27. 
